name: MLCreateError
desc: The errors Create ML throws while performing various operations, such as training models, making predictions, writing models to a file system, and so on.

items.name: case cancelled
items.desc: An error that indicates you canceled the training session.

items.name: case incompatibleParameters(parameter: String, originalValue: String, newValue: String)
items.desc: An error that indicates the training session parameters are incompatible.

items.name: case modifiedTrainingData
items.desc: An error that indicates the training data is different from the data when you created the session.

items.name: case io(reason: String)
items.desc: An error that indicates an I/O failure.

items.name: case type(reason: String)
items.desc: An error that indicates a missing or incorrect type.

items.name: case generic(reason: String)
items.desc: An error that indicates a failure not covered by one of the other errors.

items.name: let MLCreateErrorDomain: String
items.desc: A global constant that defines the domain for Create ML errors.

items.name: var description: String
items.desc: A human-readable description of the error.

items.name: var debugDescription: String
items.desc: A human-readable description of the error thatâ€™s suitable for output during debugging.

items.name: static var errorDomain: String
items.desc: The domain name for Create ML errors.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A localized, human-readable description of the error.

items.name: var errorCode: Int
items.desc: The numeric code of this error.

items.name: var errorUserInfo: [String : Any]
items.desc: A dictionary that provides additional information about the error.

items.name: var errorDescription: String?
items.desc: A localized, human-readable description of the error and why it occurred, if applicable.

items.name: var failureReason: String?
items.desc: A localized, human-readable reason behind the failure, if applicable.

items.name: var helpAnchor: String?
items.desc: The help anchor for the error message in the user interface, if applicable.

items.name: var recoverySuggestion: String?
items.desc: A localized, human-readable suggestion to address the failure, if applicable.
